  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting media diversity, media literacy adoption and community media development in Gabon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The new communication law adopted in 2016 recognizes community media. In line with the law and UNESCO Community Media Sustainability Policy series, the office will support the drafting of a national strategy for community media sustainability.
Gabon is one of the country in Central Africa region that has adapted and integrated the MIL modules for teacher. Further actions regarding adoption and integration of MIL will focus on youth associations (training on MIL) and secondary education level (development of learning materials). 
Through organization of World Radio Day, the office will mobilize stakeholders and advocate for media pluralism.</narrative>
  </description>
